<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-24T17:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="444" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d444">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to the Presidents Special
                                    Assistant</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hopkins</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d444fn1">Attached to this document is the following note by Hopkins
                                    dated April 10, 1943: “This is a memorandum Churchill handed me
                                    at Casablanca.”</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi></placeName>,] <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1943-01-24T23:59:59+01:00" notBefore="1943-01-12T00:00:00+01:00">undated</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I suggest that U.S. Chiefs of Staff should be informed that shipments
                                on ground equipment and aircraft to the French should only be
                                undertaken at a rate to be determined by Combined Chiefs of Staff
                                which will not prejudice military operations agreed on at
                                Casablanca.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>